cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.ET, cs.SE, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the design, training, and deployment of AI systems, which are all related to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the potential harms caused by AI systems in complex social contexts, which falls under the category of cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY). The authors also discuss the incorporation of dissent and democratic institutions in the development pipeline, which relates to ethical issues in technology (cs.ET) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes the cultivation of virtues by those responsible for development, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
